<paragraph blockId="26.[144,1104,1645,1701]" lastBlockId="27.[212,1172,1188,1692]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="1295" pageId="26" pageNumber="1294">
Shield (
<figureCitation box="[230,362,1645,1669]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" captionTargetId="figure-229@27.[213,1170,172,981]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 11. Pagurixus cavicarpus sp. nov. holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1294">Figure 11A</figureCitation>
) about 1.1 times as long as broad; anterior margin between rostrum and lateral projections weakly concave; anterolateral margins sloping; dorsal surface slightly convex, with few tufts of setae laterally; lateral margins moderately convex. Rostrum triangular, well produced, far overreaching lateral projections, terminating acutely. Lateral projections obsolete, each with minute submarginal spinule.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295" startId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" targetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph blockId="27.[212,1172,1011,1121]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">
Figure 11. 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2010" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2010" box="[332,545,1011,1033]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pagurixus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicarpus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,545,1011,1033]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">Pagurixus cavicarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,639,1012,1033]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="27.[212,1172,1188,1692]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">
Ocular peduncles (
<figureCitation box="[464,595,1316,1340]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" captionTargetId="figure-229@27.[213,1170,172,981]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 11. Pagurixus cavicarpus sp. nov. holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">Figure 11A</figureCitation>
) stout, about 0.7 length of shield, each with row of tufts of stiff setae on dorsal surface (setae at base of cornea not extending beyond distal corneal margin); corneas slightly dilated, corneal width about 0.5 of peduncular length; basal part very slightly inflated, but narrower than corneal width. Ocular acicles subtriangular, each with minute submarginal spinule concealed by distal projection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[212,1172,1188,1692]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">
Antennular peduncles (
<figureCitation box="[517,647,1508,1532]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" captionTargetId="figure-229@27.[213,1170,172,981]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 11. Pagurixus cavicarpus sp. nov. holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">Figure 11A</figureCitation>
) overreaching distal corneal margins by about 0.3 length of ultimate segment. Ultimate segment with tufts of long setae on dorsolateral distal portion; ventral surface with two longitudinal rows of dense short setae (setae directed outward) (
<figureCitation box="[498,628,1604,1628]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" captionTargetId="figure-229@27.[213,1170,172,981]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 11. Pagurixus cavicarpus sp. nov. holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">Figure 11B</figureCitation>
). Basal segment with minute laterodistal spinule on statocyst lobe. Ventral flagellum (
<figureCitation box="[627,755,1636,1660]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="27.[212,279,1011,1033]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,173,981]" captionTargetId="figure-229@27.[213,1170,172,981]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 11. Pagurixus cavicarpus sp. nov. holotype, ovigerous female (shield length 2.3 mm; FMNH 1710). (A) Shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) ultimate segment and ventral flagellum of left antennule, ventral view; (C) left fourth pereopod, lateral view; (D) sixth thoracic sternite, ventral view; (E) telson, dorsal view. Notes: Scale bars, (A) 1 mm; (B–E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209631/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1295">Figure 11B</figureCitation>
) with dense long setae on lateral and mesial margins.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209633" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5209633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209633/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1296" startId="28.[144,211,1523,1545]" targetBox="[146,1101,169,1493]" targetPageId="28">
